            "headline": "Strategic and innovative global executive who delivers sustainable value to shareholders, customers, and employees.",
            "summary": "Paul is a C-Level executive and Board member with year-after-year success achieving revenue and profit targets in Fortune 100, private-, and mid-tier specialty chemicals and engineered materials industries with demonstrated success of developing and executing winning strategies for business growth.  Over 20 years of multi-site, global specialty business leadership with companies like Lydall (LDL, now Alkegen), Jacob Holm (private, now Glatfelter), Clarcor (CLC, now Parker Hannifin), and Ahlstrom Oy (AHL.HEL).  He is a long-standing Board member of INDA, the nonwovens and engineered fabrics industry association, presiding as Chairman in 2010-2012 and 2020.\n\nSpecialties: Global business strategy; financial and operational leadership; innovation platform development and execution; strategic partnerships; turn-around initiatives; strategic deployment and team alignment; driving profitable, sustainable growth.",
